Maybe that's what they're going for, sometimes you make a call with your gut and it's the wrong one and people die, but in a game that's just frustrating.

I've put a handful of hours into this game and it's great! It's fundamentally a resource management game using police and detectives. I can't give it 5 stars, though, because if I didn't have a Galaxy Note phone with a stylus, this would be frustrating to play on a phone - recommend you only play on a tablet or with a stylus. The developer has done a great job otherwise but should adjust the sizing of the interface elements to improve mobile usability. Also - THANK YOU for the lack of IAP!

This game is awesome and I can't wait for the second one to arrive(please hurry).
